Date: 25-10-2025 & 28-10-2025

Aim
To create two threads that compute squares for odd numbers and cubes for even numbers.
To synchronize threads to print outputs alternately in order from 1..n.
To demonstrate inter-thread coordination using wait/notify.
Algorithm
Read integer n (upper limit).
Use a shared object with current number i=1.
Thread Square: when i is odd, print square and increment i; else wait.
Thread Cube: when i is even, print cube and increment i; else wait.
Use synchronized block with wait/notifyAll for coordination.
Stop when i > n and notify waiting threads to exit.
Join threads and end program.
Program (Java)
import java.util.*;
public class SquaresCubesThreads {
    static class Shared {
        int i = 1, n;
        Shared(int n){ this.n = n; }
    }
    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        Shared s = new Shared(n);
        Thread square = new Thread(() -> {
            synchronized (s) {
                while (s.i <= s.n) {
                    try {
                        if (s.i % 2 == 1) {
                            System.out.println("Square: " + (s.i * s.i));
                            s.i++;
                            s.notifyAll();
                        } else s.wait();
                    } catch (InterruptedException e) { Thread.currentThread().interrupt(); }
                }
                s.notifyAll();
            }
        });
        Thread cube = new Thread(() -> {
            synchronized (s) {
                while (s.i <= s.n) {
                    try {
                        if (s.i % 2 == 0) {
                            System.out.println("Cube: " + (s.i * s.i * s.i));
                            s.i++;
                            s.notifyAll();
                        } else s.wait();
                    } catch (InterruptedException e) { Thread.currentThread().interrupt(); }
                }
                s.notifyAll();
            }
        });
        square.start();
        cube.start();
        square.join();
        cube.join();
        sc.close();
    }
}



Sample Output
Square: 1
Cube: 8
Result
Demonstrated coordinated multithreading output sequence.
Printed squares for odd and cubes for even up to n.
